<br>
Example:<br>
<br>
Normal DD 50th lvl wizard 20 percent debuff<br>
Normal DD 51st lvl wizard 25 percent debuff<br>
Normal DD 52nd lvl wizard 30 percent debuff<br>
Normal DD 53rd lvl wizard 35 percent debuff<br>
Normal DD 54th lvl wizard 40 percent debuff<br>
.........<br>
Normal DD 60th lvl wizard 70 percent debuff<br>
<br>
Now for Lures:<br>
<br>
Lure Level 52 60 percent Debuff<br>
Lure level 55 90 percent Debuff<br>
Lure level 58 120 percent Debuff (Yes no resists then)<br>
Lure level 60 140 percent Debuff (Yes no resists then)<br>
<br>
So by using this chart Wizards DD would be just like what Verant says we are.  Masters of magical damage.  Using the correct Lure spell at level 57 it would be unresistable on the mob.  While on the other hand using our normal DD spells they would only have a 30 percent chance of not hitting a highly resistant mob.<br>
<br>
This would make me believe in our DD ability once again.  These are just a few ideas, if they don't want to up damage, then just lower the resists wizards get using those spells.  That is not going to unbalance the class, it will just make us true masters of direct damage once again.  (We are now, but only by a very very slim margin) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uroclarlorestar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roclar Lorestar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/16/01 3:35:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=432.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> I should add this</span><hr size=1> For those of you that don't know.  Our normal DD spells as it sits right now have NO debuff and have the same resists as other spells.  Only with our lure line of spells do we have lower resists than other DD casters. <br>
<br>
Absor stated, awhile back, that there was no such thing as when we hit level 35 our spells have a innate debuff ability.  In essence our normall DD spells have the same resists as the other casters of DD.<br>
<br>
Hehe, that is why when you see the Cleric nuke his spells are not highly resisted like yours.  They are the same resists.  <br>
<br>
I thought I would add this for those that did not know about this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwolandgrauensturm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Woland Grauensturm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/21/01 4:58:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=432.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I should add this</span><hr size=1> <br>
